-- E.ON Plans to Sell $4.5 Billion Gazprom Stake to Russia's VEB, Open Market
-- B y   A n n a   S h i r y a e v s k a y a   a n d   S t e p h e n   B i e r m a n
-- 2010-12-01T12:54:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-01/e-on-said-to-have-agreed-sale-of-3-5-stake-in-gazprom-to-russian-bank-veb.html
E.ON AG reached an agreement in
principle to sell its 3.5 percent stake in OAO Gazprom to VEB,
Russia’s development bank, said two people familiar with the
talks.  The deal may be announced as soon as today, the two people
said, declining to be identified because the talks are
confidential and aren’t yet complete.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Anna Shiryaevskaya  in Moscow at 
 ashiryaevska@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Kennedy at   wkennedy3@bloomberg.net  